<subSubSection id="A1D565563F7CFFEBFF26FEC0FB09FC09" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7CFFEBFF26FEC0FDA4FDF5" blockId="73.[151,1437,290,1000]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Morphology. D VI (V–VI) + I,7–9; A I,6–9; P 13–17 (Miller 1986). Small goby with subcylindrical body, laterally compressed towards caudal fin, 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7CFFEBFD85FEECFF32FE49" bold="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">head slightly depressed and distinctly small compared to thickness of body</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F7CFFEBFF02FE08FED8FE48" box="[227,312,398,425]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-351@73.[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 63. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Pomatoschistus bathi. Photo by R. Pillon, Rab Island, Croatia, northern Adriatic Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601757/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Snout moderately long. Eyes dorsolateral, interorbital space moderately narrow. Caudal peduncle slender, clearly lower than body depth. The first dorsal fin about equal or shorter than the second dorsal fin, with more or less rounded distal margin. Caudal fin rounded. Scales present on body, usually visible on close-up photographs at least dorsally. Predorsal area naked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7CFFEBFF26FD98FF24FCD4" blockId="73.[151,1437,290,1000]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Live coloration. Body from beige to light brown with pale saddles and mottled patterning dorsally and white ventrally, with vertical, iridescent, pale gray streaks. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7CFFEBFD0FFDC7FAC7FD61" bold="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Five small pale dorsal saddles ending ventrally above the midline not linked with a midlateral irregularly shaped, horizontally elongate, black spot below</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F7CFFEBFAD8FDE0FA6FFD60" box="[1337,1423,614,641]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-351@73.[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 63. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Pomatoschistus bathi. Photo by R. Pillon, Rab Island, Croatia, northern Adriatic Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601757/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Each black lateral spot with a short ventral black extension, except the last, pear-shaped, at caudal-fin base. Short dark dash from the center of the snout to the upper lip, not always visible. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7CFFEBFC13FD2BFC42FD0D" bold="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Indistinct gray to dark vertical bar extending from ventral edge of eye to corner of mouth; cheek pale</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F7CFFEBFC50FD54FBE4FD0C" box="[945,1028,722,749]" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-351@73.[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 63. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Pomatoschistus bathi. Photo by R. Pillon, Rab Island, Croatia, northern Adriatic Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601757/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7CFFEBFBF9FD57FABCFCEE" bold="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">On side of head, between opercle and upper pectoral-fin base, a horizontal, Y-shaped brown to reddish marking, branching forward</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F7CFFEBFA8EFD70FF56FCD4" captionStart="FIGURE 63" captionStartId="73.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-351@73.[172,1416,1024,1854]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURE 63. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Pomatoschistus bathi. Photo by R. Pillon, Rab Island, Croatia, northern Adriatic Sea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601757" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601757/files/figure.png" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7CFFEBFF26FCB8FB66FCB9" blockId="73.[151,1437,290,1000]" box="[199,1158,830,856]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
